        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 1:55PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 154 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mayersville, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Cary and Mayersville around 200 PM CDT.
Rolling Fork around 205 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
northeastern Louisiana...and central and west central Mississippi.</instruction>
